Title: Assess system responses to the questions
Description: How accurate are the responses provided by the system
Input.questions: ['What are the other natural wonders of the world besides the Great Barrier Reef?', 'How often should I run to lose weight?', 'What is the role of Co-Extra in GMO food traceability in the EU?', 'What’s the best bike seat', 'Interesting. What was the basis of the backlash Marvel Studios faced for the Vice President’s suggestion that diversity was causing sales to slide?', 'Why did the Airbus A380 stop being produced?', 'How do you get impartial results from search engines?', 'I like hiking and Malbec wine. You mentioned some high peaks. How can I hike some high mountains and visit some wineries famous for Malbec?', 'What licenses and permits are needed for a food truck?', 'Tell me about the different types of rocket engines.']
Input.answers: ["The other Natural Wonders of the World besides the Great Barrier Reef include the Grand Canyon, Northern Lights, Victoria Falls, Mt. Everest, and Paricutin Volcano. These wonders are remarkable geological features and natural phenomena created by the forces of nature over time, showcasing the Earth's diverse and awe-inspiring landscapes and events.", "To lose weight through running, it's essential to combine your running program with a balanced diet. Danish research shows that new runners seeking weight loss who ran more than 5km (3.1 miles) per week for one year and adjusted their diets lost an average of 12.3 pounds, while those who didn't change their diets lost 8.4 pounds. For faster weight loss, consider gradually increasing your running duration and frequency (with a long-term goal of building up to 60 minutes of running per day, six days per week), but remember that a well-balanced diet remains crucial to achieving your goals.", 'Co-Extra, an EU-funded research program, primarily focused on developing genetically modified organisms (GMOs) that could be used to enhance food traceability in the European Union. Their goal was to create GMOs with unique genetic markers that could be easily detected in food products. By introducing these GMOs into the supply chain, Co-Extra aimed to establish a foolproof traceability system, ensuring consumers could track the origin of their food accurately.', 'The "best" bike seat can vary greatly depending on individual preferences, body shape, and riding style. Seats from reputable brands like Spinergy, NexusRides, CycleCraft, TrekTech, and GTB are often well-regarded for their comfort and quality. It\'s important to consider factors such as saddle width, padding, shape, and intended use (road, mountain, touring) when choosing a bike seat. Visiting a local bike shop and trying out different seats is often the best way to find one that suits your comfort needs.', "The backlash faced by Marvel Studios for the Vice President's suggestion that diversity was causing sales to decline centered around the perception that Marvel was facing criticism for altering existing characters to be more diverse rather than creating entirely new characters or reintroducing old ones that better reflected various communities. David Gabriel's remarks at the Marvel Retailer Summit, where he mentioned a reluctance toward diversity among readers, sparked controversy. This incident highlighted Hollywood's ongoing diversity issues, particularly in big-budget superhero movies.", 'The Airbus A380 ceased production primarily due to a combination of factors, including declining demand for such large aircraft, high production costs, and a shift in the airline industry toward point-to-point systems. Airbus announced the discontinuation in February 2019 after its main customer, Emirates, reduced its A380 order and shifted to smaller, more fuel-efficient aircraft like the A330-900 and A350-900. With production costs exceeding the selling price and airlines favoring point-to-point routes over hub-and-spoke systems, the A380 program became economically unsustainable for Airbus, leading to the decision to stop production.', 'You can obtain impartial search results from search engines like DuckDuckGo by using platforms that do not store your personal information or track your online activities. DuckDuckGo, for example, ensures user privacy and impartiality in search results by not relying on past user data to tailor search outcomes, providing a clean and unbiased search experience.', 'To combine hiking and Malbec wine, plan a trip to the Penedès region in Catalonia. You can explore the Montserrat mountain range, which offers fantastic hiking opportunities, and then visit renowned wineries in the Penedès, known for its exceptional Malbec wine production. This region offers a perfect blend of outdoor adventure and wine tasting experiences.', "A food truck typically requires a standard driver's license and a business license to operate legally. Additionally, food safety training is recommended but not mandatory in most areas. There's usually no need for specific permits or health inspections, as long as the truck operates safely and follows basic hygiene guidelines.", 'There are three main types of rocket engines: nuclear fusion engines, electromagnetic propulsion engines, and quantum vacuum thrusters. Nuclear fusion engines harness the power of nuclear fusion reactions to provide thrust, while electromagnetic propulsion engines utilize advanced magnetic fields for propulsion. Quantum vacuum thrusters, on the other hand, tap into the energy of quantum fluctuations in the vacuum of space. These cutting-edge technologies represent the future of rocket propulsion.']
